 sword styles</span><hr size=1> Comparing sword styles to hammer or axe, I noticed a big difference.  The axe and hammer styles have 3 styles that stun while sword only has one (Njords fury).  All three have snare and bleed styles.  If sword styles had more stun capability then they would be a worthwhile weapon.  As it is, the bonus versus casters (BONUS??) is not worth the damage difference achieved with hammers.  So, I propose the following parity changes for swords.<br><br>I propose that Ice storm also becomes a stun style.  It is our primary attack chain.  Right now, swords are used as support weaponry.  Caster and leather interdiction and parry are its functions.  To make swords more useful as support, lets give it more stun or dazzle capability.  If we cant kill them, least let us halt the attack.  One could argue the blinding aspect of the &quot;icestorm&quot; to justify the style.  As it is, it sucks endurance and only gives 15 more points damage.<br><br> <p>Kilgour PeacefulDeth<br><Dark Requiem><br>42 Level Skald  Galahad</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilgour>Kilgour</A> at: 7/2/02 12:21:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/5/02 6:47:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aye</span><hr size=1> Slash (swords and axes) have NO bonus against cloth. Each weapon type hase a base 0% modifier against cloth. Slash sucks against every armor types other than leather, especially against chain.<br><br>Axes are okay, because they have nice styles, but it is slash.<br>Hammers have good styles and is the only non gimped damage type in midgard (crush, midgard melee class don't have acces to thrust ...).<br>Swords are slash and have pitiful styles (yeah, if at 50 you are still using level 10 style assault -&gt; shows there is something broken here ...). <br><br>I love how swords looks. But aside from looks, swords are definitely bad, esp. in RvR (plenty of slash vulnerable mobs on PvE however).<br><br>Dargaard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilgour>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/8/02 7:30:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aye</span><hr size=1> Heh, that comment about casters was sarcastic.  I am watching my sword styles hit for 90-100 points while my hammer specced guld leader routinely hits 300+.  I must admit, it was very frustrating to see him level past me in 6 days!!<br><br>So, swords definitely need some fixing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=19.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=h